               <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib69-1">La litterature sur lui est abondante : BHO, 392- 93 ; PO, XVIII et XIX ; Barsaum,
Lu'lu '2 , 325-26; BSO, I, 1017-18 (J.M. Fiey).
D. Bundy, dans Le Museon 91 (1978), 45- 86.
Sur Je rapt de son corps, de Qasiun a Psilta, en 622, cf. M.A. Kugener dans ROC
7 (1902) , 196-217.</quote>
               </note>
               <note type="abstract">Jacob Baradaeus was a monk who born near Phesilta. The Syrian Orthodox or Jacobite church was named for him. He ordained a separate hierarchy of Miaphysite clergy. He also negotiated with the empress Theodora and Harith, the Ghassanid client king. He was ordained by Theodosius of Alexandria and travelled extensively to revive the Miaphysite clergy.</note>
